<author><name><![CDATA[Dwedit]]></name></author>
<updated>2011-04-20T12:13:08-07:00</updated>
<published>2011-04-20T12:13:08-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7669&amp;p=77013#p77013</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7669&amp;p=77013#p77013"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Japanese Gimmick! on a PAL console]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7669&amp;p=77013#p77013"><![CDATA[
Game genie code ALEAAUAO will transpose the square waves and triangle waves up by one half step (it changes CLC to SEC before an ADC)<br />Game genie code ALUANOAO will transpose the "FME7" sound channels up one half step.<br />But even with those two minor changes, the sound is still off key with the DMC channel, still slightly too low for the DMC channel's pitch.<br /><br />Also: GVVTEXIS fixes the status bar.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Wed Apr 20, 2011 12:13 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
